<h4>HEALTH</h4>

<ul><li><a target="_blank"  href="https://twitter.com/chrisvanderveen/status/1770195345374384209"><strong>CU board gets an earful about medical debt.</strong></a><strong> </strong>Community members and advocates working with the <strong>Center for Health Progress</strong> showed up at a meeting of the <strong>University of Colorado Hospital Authority</strong> on Tuesday to protest <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2024/02/19/uchealth-debt-collectors/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=*|MC:SUBJECT|*_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">UCHealth&#8217;s practice of suing patients</a>.<strong><br></strong><strong>â€” Chris Vanderveen (via X/Twitter)</strong></li>

